<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/contrib.entomol.73.e109883.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Lepidostoma diespiter (Malicky & Sangpradub, 2001). A-C. Male genitalia: A. Dorsal; B. Ventral; C. Left lateral. D. Head with scape; E. Forewing; F. Phallic apparatus. AD = apicodorsal process of inferior appendage (paired); AV = apicoventral process of inferior appendage (paired); BDP = Basodorsal process of inferior appendage (paired); BP = two basal processes of antennal scape (paired); IFA = inferior appendage (paired); IX seg. = segment; PA = phallic paramere (paired); PH = phallus; X Seg = segment X." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/941755" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

